###Switching the rows

For the given matrix, $R_2$ and $R_3$ are given below. 

$R_2=\left[\begin{array} {ccc}
3 & 0 & 0 & -2  \end{array} \right] ~~~~~ R_3=\left[\begin{array} {ccc}
1 & 1 & 7 & -3  \end{array} \right]$

$\left[\begin{array} {ccc}
5 & -2 & 1 & 1 \\
3 & 0 & 0 & -2 \\
1 & 1 & 7 & -3 \end{array} \right]  \xrightarrow{R_3 \leftrightarrow R_2}\left[\begin{array} {ccc}
5 & -2 & 1 & 1 \\
1 & 1 & 7 & -3 \\
3 & 0 & 0 & -2 \end{array} \right] $

###Adding the Corresponding Terms 

$\large{\begin{align}\left[ \begin{array}{cc}
\blueE{2} & \greenE{-1} & \redD{3} \\
\goldD{1} & \maroonC{2} & \tealD{3}
\end{array} \right]-\left[ \begin{array}{cc}
\blueE{3} & \greenE{3} & \redD{1} \\
\goldD{3} & \maroonC{1} & \tealD{0}
\end{array} \right]&= 
\left[ \begin{array}{cc}
(\blueE{2-3}) & (\greenE{-1-3}) & (\redD{3-1}) \\
(\goldD{1-3}) & (\maroonC{2-1}) & (\tealD{3-0})
\end{array} \right]
\\\\&=\left[ \begin{array}{cc}
\blueE{-1} & \greenE{-4} & \redD{2} \\
\goldD{-2} & \maroonC{1} & \tealD{3}
\end{array} \right]\end{align}}$

options.explanation:
If we have a matrix $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr} \blueE{A_{11}} & \greenE{A_{12}}
\\ \goldD{A_{21}} & \maroonC{A_{22}} \end{array}\right]$, and a constant $k$, then we can multiply $k$ and $A$ by multiplying each term of $A$ by $k$. 

$kA=\left[\begin{array}{rr} k\blueE{A_{11}} & k\greenE{A_{12}}
\\ k\goldD{A_{21}} & k\maroonC{A_{22}} \end{array}\right]$

hints.content:
###Multiplying each term 

$ \Large{\begin{align}8\cdot \left[\begin{array}{rr} \blueE{2} & \greenE{-1} & \redD{3}
\\ \goldD{1} & \maroonC{2} & \tealD{3} \end{array}\right]&=\left[\begin{array}{rr} 8\cdot\blueE{2} & 8\cdot\greenE{-1} & 8\cdot\redD{3}
\\ 8\cdot\goldD{1} & 8\cdot\maroonC{2}  & 8\cdot\tealD{3} \end{array}\right]
\\\\&=\left[\begin{array}{rr} \blueE{16} & \greenE{-8} & \redD{24}
\\ \goldD{8} & \maroonC{16} & \tealD{24} \end{array}\right]\end{align}}$

###Finding the Determinant of $A$ 

$\begin{align}\det{A}&=\det{\left[\begin{array}{rr} \blueD{33} & \maroonD{21}
\\ \maroonD{1} & \blueD{-2} \end{array}\right]} 
\\\\&=\blueD{33\cdot(-2)}-\maroonD{21\cdot1}
\\\\&=\blueD{-66}-\maroonD{21}
\\\\&=-87\end{align}$
